Interface Class.Super<O,J,D extends Class<O,J>>

  • Type Parameters:
    O - the ontology.
    J - the type of Ground and EntitySet managed by this Descriptor.
    D - the type of Class descriptor instantiated during buildSuperClasses() ()} through getSuperClassDescriptor(Object, Object).
    All Superinterfaces:
    Axiom, Axiom.Descriptor<O,J>, Class<O,J>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ClassExpression.Super<D>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FullClassDesc, HierarchicalClassDesc
    Enclosing interface:
    Class<O,J>

    public static interface Class.Super<O,J,D extends Class<O,J>>
extends Class<O,J>
    Implementation of this interface enables a Class to have the Class.Super expression.

      • readAxioms

        default java.util.List<Axiom.MappingIntent> readAxioms()
        Description copied from interface: Axiom.Descriptor
        This method is used to update specific Axiom.EntitySet (or Axiom.ExpressionEntitySet) by synchronizing the internal state of the descriptor with the queried OWL structure, such that they are equal. It is based on EntitySet#synchroniseFrom(EntitySet).
        Specified by:
        readAxioms in interface Axiom.Descriptor<O,J>
        Returns:
        the changes made in the Axiom.EntitySet during the reading. Note that the elements of the returned list, may not have the Axiom.MappingIntent.getOntologyChanges() field initialised (i.e.: Void).

      • buildSuperClasses

        default java.util.Set<D> buildSuperClasses()
        Create an Axiom.Descriptor set where each element represents the super classes of this Class. Each of those Classs are instantiated through the method getSuperClassDescriptor(Object, Object); this is called for all getSuperClasses().
        Returns:
        the set of Classs that describes the super entities of this described ontological class.

      • getSuperClassDescriptor

        D getSuperClassDescriptor(J instance,
                          O ontology)
        This method is called by buildSuperClasses() and its purpose is to instantiate a new Class to represent an super class of this Class Descriptor.
        Parameters:
        instance - the instance to ground the new Class.
        ontology - the ontology in which ground the new Class.
        Returns:
        a new Axiom.Descriptor for all the super classes of this descriptor.

      • synchroniseSuperClassesToExpressionAxioms

        default Axiom.EntitySet.SynchronisationIntent<J> synchroniseSuperClassesToExpressionAxioms()
        It calls EntitySet#synchroniseTo(EntitySet) with querySuperClasses() as input parameter. This computes the changes to be performed in the OWL representation for synchronise it with respect to getSuperClasses(). This should be done by Axiom.Descriptor.writeAxioms().
        Returns:
        the changes to be done to synchronise this structure with the super classes of an OWL class.

      • synchroniseSuperClassesFromExpressionAxioms

        default Axiom.EntitySet.SynchronisationIntent<J> synchroniseSuperClassesFromExpressionAxioms()
        It calls EntitySet#synchroniseFrom(EntitySet) with querySuperClasses() as input parameter. This computes the changes to be performed into the getSuperClasses() in order to synchronise it with respect to an OWL representation. This is be done by readAxioms().
        Returns:
        the changes to be done to synchronise the super classes of an OWL class with this structure.
